ope all this indulgence won't develope the faults in Cynthia's character. It's a week since we heard from her, and I did write so particularly to ask her for the autumn fashions before I bought my new bonnet. But riches are a great snare.\"\"Be thankful you are spared temptation, my dear.\"\"No, I'm not. Everybody likes to be tempted. And, after all, it's very easy to resist temptation, if one wishes.\"\"I don't find it so easy,\" said her husband.\"Here's medicine for you, mamma,\" said Molly, entering with a letter held up in her hand. \"A letter from Cynthia.\"\n","------\n","In this paragraph, a woman named Cynthia is being discussed by two people, one of whom is her mother. The mother expresses regret that Cynthia did not end up with the person she is speaking to, as she believes he would have been more successful and lived in London. However, Cynthia is now with someone else who can take her to Paris and other places. The mother worries that this indulgence may negatively affect Cynthia's character. The conversation then shifts to the mother's desire for Cynthia to send her\n","------\n","\n","\n","832\n","\"Come, come! Remember I belong to the last generation,\" said Mr. Gibson.\"And Cynthia will not notice what I wear,\" said Molly, bright with pleasure at the thought of seeing her again.\"No! but Walter will. He has such a quick eye for dress, and I think I rival papa; if he's a good stepfather, I'm a good stepmother, and I could not bear to see my Molly shabby, and not looking her best. I must have a new gown too. It won't do to look as if we had nothing but the dresses which we wore at the wedding!\"But Molly stood out against the new gown for herself, and urged that if Cynthia and Walter were to come to visit them often, they had better see them as they really were, in dress, habits, and appointments. When Mr. Gibson had left the room, Mrs. Gibson softly reproached Molly for her obstinacy.\"You might have allowed me to beg for a new gown for you, Molly, when you knew how much I had admired that figured silk at Brown's the other day. And now, of course, I can't be so selfish as to get it for myself, and you to have nothing. You should learn to understand the wishes of other people. Still, on the whole, you are a dear, sweet girl, and I only wish--well, I know what I wish; only dear papa does not like it to be talked about. And now cover me up close, and let me go to sleep, and dream about my dear Cynthia and my new shawl!\"\n","------\n","Mr. Gibson and Molly are discussing their upcoming visit from Cynthia and Walter. Molly is excited to see Cynthia again and believes that Cynthia won't notice what Molly is wearing. However, Mr. Gibson points out that Walter has a keen eye for dress and Molly should look her best. Molly disagrees and argues that they should present themselves as they truly are. After Mr. Gibson leaves, Mrs. Gibson reproaches Molly for not allowing her to beg for a new gown for Molly. Mrs. Gibson expresses her\n","------\n","\n","\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["print(len(summaries))\n","print(len(df))\n","print(summaries[183])\n","\n"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"7bnL2SEJdij3","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1693169135303,"user_tz":240,"elapsed":148,"user":{"displayName":"Eliza Thornton","userId":"13738708515567558230"}},"outputId":"3d768e68-84d5-49a0-c9bd-f5217adfcaeb"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["833\n","833\n","Molly remembers being in the room where her dying mother was and seeing her pale, wan face surrounded by white linen. She often imagines her mother's face and form in the room, and these visions bring her comfort. Now, the room has been changed with new furniture and a grand toilette-table.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["df[\"Summary\"] = summaries\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"B3kI5J54dWLg"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n","file_name = '/content/drive/My Drive/WiBD/Project_2/less data/summary2.csv'\n","df.to_csv(file_name, mode='a', header = False, index=False)\n","\n"],"metadata":{"id":"IVwt1UGMZ1ri"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n","\n","**Now read the summaries back in and summarize into Layer 2 of summaries.**"],"metadata":{"id":"bmxdducbMRQU"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["column_headings = ['Chapter', 'Paragraph', 'Text', \"Summary1\"]\n","df = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/My Drive/WiBD/Project_2/less data/summary2.csv', header=None, index_col=None, names=column_headings)\n","df.head()"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":206},"id":"EVDe_tRPyj0Q","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1693659156182,"user_tz":240,"elapsed":2129,"user":{"displayName":"Eliza Thornton","userId":"13738708515567558230"}},"outputId":"8f1e5826-7336-4088-ef9b-3edfcbbbb963"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["   Chapter  Paragraph                                               Text  \\\n","0        1          1  I.THE DAWN OF A GALA DAY.To begin with the old...   \n","1        1          2  Molly Gibson saw all this, but all she thought...   \n","2        1          3  Now, as the countess was absent from the Tower...   \n","3        1          4  For the first time in her life, Molly Gibson w...   \n","4        1          5  \"Your daughter, eh, Gibson?--nice little girl,...   \n","\n","                                            Summary1  \n","0  In this paragraph, the story begins by describ...  \n","1  Molly Gibson is excited for a special event in...  \n","2  The countess of the Towers enlists the help of...  \n","3  Molly Gibson, a young girl, is invited to the ...  \n","4  The paragraph is about a conversation between ...  "],"text/html":["\n","  <div id=\"df-97a543b3-005b-45ff-be79-1b94eb6e6d5e\" class=